lows and we find no definitive evidence that favours one process over the\nother. Although highly uncertain, we derive mass outflow rates (typically ~10x\nthe SFRs), kinetic energies (~0.5-10% of L[AGN]) and momentum rates (typically\n>~10-20x L[AGN]/c) consistent with theoretical models that predict AGN-driven\noutflows play a significant role in shaping the evolution of galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Mar 2014 20:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Apr 2014 09:04:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 1 May 2014 08:49:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
